radiographic_examinations.findings: Lung bases demonstrate dependent atelectasis. Several subcentimeter hypodensities in the liver too small to characterize but most likely simple cysts. Gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, bilateral kidneys, and bilateral adrenals are unremarkable. Incidental note of a circumaortic left renal vein. Abdominal aorta is of normal caliber. Stomach and loops of small bowel are normal. Large bowel has moderate fecal loading. Bladder, prostate, and rectum are unremarkable. The appendix is fluid filled, up to 1.2 cm with hyperemic wall and surrounding inflammatory changes. No evidence of perforation or fluid collection. No suspicious or aggressive appearing bony lesions.
